6. Planned changes to improve safety.

The Peru Facility has an on-going commitment to improve safety and protect the environment. In addition to scheduled internal company audits and inspections, the Peru Facility performs an annual self-evaluation as a Star Site in OSHA's Voluntary Protection Program. The following health, safety and environmental improvements are anticipated during the next several years based on our most recent VPP recertification inspection:
- Installation of a SIL II SIS overfill protection system on the pentane storage tanks;
- Improved protection of our shipping dock doors as related to walking and working surfaces;
- Improved fall protection systems for ladders used to access the top of buildings, bins, tanks etc.;
- Improvements in guarding systems in the packaging area and;
- Additional ergonomics assessments and improvements in the packaging area.
